<h4>Dependencies</h4>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Optional, but officially supported dependencies for Jumpstart Pro applications.</p>

<div class="mt-8 space-y-5">
  <div class="form-picker-group toggle">
    <%= check_box_tag "configuration[gems][]", "acts_as_tenant", Jumpstart.config.gems.include?("acts_as_tenant"), id: "acts_as_tenant" %>
    <div>
      <label for="acts_as_tenant">ActsAsTenant</label>
      <p><%= link_to "ActsAsTenant", "https://github.com/erwinm/acts_as_tenant", target: :_blank %> provides row-level, scalable multitenancy for Rails.</p>
      <p>See the <%= link_to "Accounts & Multitenancy", accounts_docs_path, target: :_blank %> docs to learn how to use ActsAsTenant.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-picker-group toggle">
    <%= check_box_tag "configuration[gems][]", "refer", Jumpstart.config.gems.include?("refer"), id: "refer" %>
    <div>
      <label for="refer">Refer</label>
      <p><%= link_to "Refer", "https://github.com/excid3/refer", target: :_blank %> Referral codes for Ruby on Rails applications.</p>
      <p>See the Users docs to learn how to use Refer.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-picker-group toggle">
    <%= check_box_tag "configuration[gems][]", "oj", Jumpstart.config.gems.include?("oj"), id: "oj" %>
    <div>
      <label for="oj">Oj</label>
      <p><%= link_to "Oj", "https://github.com/ohler55/oj", target: :_blank %> is a C extension for Ruby for fast JSON parsing.</p>
      <p>Enabling Oj will speed up Rails JSON parsing in <code>config/initializers/oj.rb</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-picker-group toggle">
    <%= check_box_tag "configuration[gems][]", "whenever", Jumpstart.config.gems.include?("whenever"), id: "whenever" %>
    <div>
      <label for="whenever">Whenever</label>
      <p><%= link_to "Whenever", "https://github.com/javan/whenever", target: :_blank %> lets you define and manage cron jobs.</p>
      <p>See <code>config/schedule.rb</code> to define cron jobs.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
